Instagram post by @noorie_rai, location: Tirumala, Andhra Pradesh, India. 28 January 2018. Photo shows someone in a yellow garment with 'Om Namah Shivay' printed repeatedly, getting head shaved by a barber. White clothing underneath. SIGNIFICANT: The 'Om Namah Shivay' (Shiva devotion) garment worn at Tirupati Balaji (Vishnu temple) connects Shaiva and Vaishnava traditions — unity of divine aspects within Hinduism itself. Aspect of Yug Parivartan: Universal Consciousness — transcending divisions even within Hindu traditions.